THE COMEDY of CRYSTAL LAKE
I. The Lowering of Crystal Lake,  II. The Biography of Archibald Jones

by a Humble Saunterer, Stacy Leroy Daniels

Announcing the release of the new book � "The Comedy of Crystal Lake" (2015); the unanticipated sequel to �The Tragedy of Crystal Lake� (1922). It's all about the 1873 lowering of Crystal Lake in Benzie County, Michigan, and a biography of Archibald Jones, the man behind the operation, and his Benzie County River Improvement Company.

Dr. Daniels describes the book as...

"Being a Summary Chronicle with Many More Sidelights, of a Tale written in Two Parts, describing a seemingly Ill-Fated Historical Event, so epochal in its nature as to have had a permanent bearing upon the development and future of Benzie County in Northwestern Lower Michigan, together with myriad viewpoints of its diverse characters and sundry locales and &c, &c."

Please see the About the Story for a short description and Writing of the Book for more details.

Lakeland Wealth Management LLC is a fee-based registered investment advisory firm based in Memphis, TN offering money management and financial planning services to families, institutions and high net worth individuals. Lakeland Wealth Management adopts fundamental value analysis and tailors the portfolios to fit individual needs, risks and time horizons. 

Sreeni Meka is the managing member and investment advisor at Lakeland Wealth Management LLC. Sreeni has twenty-three years of investment experience in the equity and derivative markets.Sreeni has worked as a management consultant for big four firms and served at a number of Fortune 500 companies in North America. Sreeni holds a Masters degree in Mechanical Engineering from The University of Texas at El Paso and an MBA degree in Finance from The University of Memphis.
